        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Balto.</placeName>
                <date>Sept. 10 5608</date>
            </p>
            <p>My dear Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><add>ב"י קבלתי</add> and thank you for it. We<lb/> only wish to have
                the form of the Inscription usual with you<lb/> was that I should make it as simple
                as possible. In <persName>Mr<lb/> Wolfries<add>?</add></persName> I have copies of a
                great many on the tombs in<lb/> some off-cities in <placeName>Germany</placeName>,
                and they are interesting,<lb/> I don't know whether you have this old work of
                his<lb/> it is interesting and is a wonderful <add>?</add> here.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have duly boted<add>?</add> your advice in regards to the<lb/>
                Lady in question. I do not know her (except a mere bow<lb/> when I meet her with her
                friends &amp; then <sic>recognise</sic> her)<lb/> but if I understand her character
                truly, in these days<lb/> of homeopathy, when <hi rend="underline"><add>?</add>
                    <add>?</add></hi> &amp;c rules every<lb/> thing she would not suit me <add>לא
                    איש דברים אנכי</add>, and how<lb/> much better the <add>?</add> so towards
                yourself and or re=<lb/>paid the talents, <add>איש חכם אתה</add> by common
                consent.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">You were kind enough to quote me a sentence from<lb/> our learned
                Fathers to support your good advice &amp;c, but<lb/> how imperative is the change
                upon you when you re-<lb/>collect the conclusion of the sentence which you seem</p>
            <pb n="1V"/>
            <p>to have forgotten: <add>בלא דירה בלא תורה בלא שלום</add> so I hope you will<lb/>
                still have this letter in <add>?</add>
                <add>כחכמתך</add> which you may<lb/> choose to be <add>?</add> in preference, you
                have at last<lb/> come to the conclusion to which long since I had come<lb/> to be
                satisfied &amp; content with what ever presents itself. I<lb/> find after all this
                is the <add>?</add> secret in life. <add>גדל מהשמח בחלקו</add><lb/>
                <add>אין לך נחת רוח</add>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">In the last <sic>occident</sic> you review—Hebrew and<lb/> English
                vocabulary I speak well of it—I was thinking of<lb/> such a look only a day or two
                before your no came for<lb/> our little children—and as you have been very kind<lb/>
                in loaning me your books from time to time, can you<lb/> spare me this that I may
                see whether it is worth while<lb/> to send for a copy. <persName>Rev. I.</persName>
                who will take this on, will<lb/> take charge of it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I do not remember whether I wrote<lb/> you in acknowledgment about
                    <persName>Eddy's</persName> names which <persName>Rabbi I.</persName> says he
                has as<lb/>
                <add>אביגדור</add>—how we should have selected this name, I know<lb/> not, and am
                rather inclined to think there is some<lb/> mistake. Bro. I. propose to see him—the
                name is good<lb/> enough and it is classical. I do not mean however,
                Bibli-<lb/>cal—but how this should have selected I know not.</p>
            <p>(as already said)<lb/> all well with us—we expect</p>
            <pb n="2R"/>
            <p>our wanderer home tomorrow, or next day after a long &amp;<lb/> pleasant sojourn at
                    <placeName>Newport</placeName> &amp;c.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Unless you come on to <placeName>Balt.</placeName> soon, we
                shall<lb/> not see you for a long time I fear, as the Holydays are<lb/> approaching.
                By the way <persName>Mr Rice</persName> told me on <date>Friday</date><lb/> that the
                new synagogue was to be consecrated <add>שבת</add><lb/> won't you be here?</p>
            <p rend="indent(7)">With <add>?</add> regard</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Joshua I. Cohen</persName>
            </p>
            <pb n="2V"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Rev. Mr Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>371 Walnut St</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p>
                <add>?</add>
            </p>
